# MCP Server

The `stake-engine-docs-mcp` server provides full-text search and retrieval of all Stake Engine documentation via the [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io). It runs locally as a stdio process and is compatible with any MCP client.

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js** 18+
- **pnpm** (recommended) or npm

## Build & Run

**1. Clone the repository**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/StakeEngine/docs.git
cd docs
```

**2. Install and build the MCP server**

```bash
cd mcp-server
pnpm install
pnpm run build
```

This runs two steps:

- `build:index` - scans all `.svx` pages and generates `data/docs-index.json`
- `build:server` - compiles TypeScript to `dist/` and copies the agent prompt

**3. Verify the server starts**

```bash
node dist/index.js
```

You should see a message like:

```
Stake Engine Docs MCP server running - 79 pages indexed (generated 2026-02-28T...)
```

Press `Ctrl+C` to stop - the server is designed to be launched by MCP clients, not run standalone.

## Client Configuration

The server communicates over **stdio**. Each MCP client has its own config file, but the format is the same - you just need the absolute path to `dist/index.js`.

<Callout type="warning">

Always use the **absolute path** to the built server. Replace `/path/to/stake-engine-docs` with the actual location on your machine.

</Callout>

### Claude Code

Create or edit `.mcp.json` in your project root:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "stake-engine-docs": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/stake-engine-docs/mcp-server/dist/index.js"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Claude Desktop

Open **Settings > Developer > Edit Config** and add to `claude_desktop_config.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "stake-engine-docs": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/stake-engine-docs/mcp-server/dist/index.js"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Cursor

Add to `.cursor/mcp.json` in your project root:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "stake-engine-docs": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/stake-engine-docs/mcp-server/dist/index.js"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Windsurf

Add to `.windsurf/mcp.json` in your project root:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "stake-engine-docs": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/stake-engine-docs/mcp-server/dist/index.js"]
    }
  }
}
```

## Tools Reference

Once connected, the MCP server exposes four tools.

<Collapsible title="search_docs - Full-text keyword search">

Full-text keyword search with weighted scoring.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `query` | string | Yes | Search query (keywords or phrase) |
| `section` | `"docs"` \| `"faq"` | No | Filter results to a section |
| `limit` | number (1–50) | No | Max results to return (default: 10) |

**Scoring weights:** title match (15), tags (6), description (4–6), route path (2), body term frequency (up to 5 per term).

</Collapsible>

<Collapsible title="get_page - Retrieve full page content">

Retrieve the full content of a documentation page.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `route` | string | Yes | Route path, e.g. `/docs/api/play` |

Returns the page title, metadata, and full body text. If the exact route is not found, suggests partial matches.

</Collapsible>

<Collapsible title="list_pages - List all pages with metadata">

List all pages with metadata.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `section` | `"docs"` \| `"faq"` | No | Filter to a section |
| `prefix` | string | No | Filter by route prefix, e.g. `/docs/api` |

</Collapsible>

<Collapsible title="get_section_tree - Navigation tree">

Get the hierarchical navigation tree.

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `section` | `"docs"` \| `"faq"` | No | Filter to a section |

</Collapsible>

## Rebuilding the Index

When documentation pages are added, edited, or removed, regenerate the search index:

```bash
cd mcp-server
pnpm run build:index
```

This re-scans all `+page.svx` files in `src/routes/docs/` and `src/routes/faq/`, parses frontmatter, cleans SVX markup, and writes `data/docs-index.json`.

<Callout type="tip">

The full `pnpm run build` command runs both `build:index` and `build:server`. Use `build:index` alone when only content changed and the server code is unchanged.

</Callout>

## Troubleshooting

<Collapsible title="Could not find docs-index.json">

The server can't locate the generated index. Make sure you ran `pnpm run build:index` first. The file should exist at `mcp-server/data/docs-index.json`.

</Collapsible>

<Collapsible title="Could not find hayden.md">

The agent prompt file is missing from the build output. Run `pnpm run build:server` - it compiles TypeScript and copies `src/hayden.md` to `dist/hayden.md`.

</Collapsible>

<Collapsible title="Tools not appearing in client">

- Verify the server starts without errors: `node /path/to/stake-engine-docs/mcp-server/dist/index.js`
- Check that the path in your client config is correct and absolute
- Restart the MCP client after changing configuration

</Collapsible>
